The EFF leadership will attend the court case of two white men, accused of assaulting a black man on a farm and forcing him into a coffin.The incident is believed to have occurred at the JM De Beer Boerdery next to Komati Power Station in Mpumalanga.EFF spokesperson Mbuyiseni Ndlozi said in a statement, &#x201C;This humiliation can be based on nothing else but his blackness, which means it is in actual fact a humiliation of black people as a whole.&#x201D;WARNING: This video contains graphic scenes which may disturb sensitive viewers.This follows a video of the incident making waves on social media and subsequently being removed from YouTube.The two men are charged with kidnapping and assault with intent to do grievous bodily harm.According to EWN the National Prosecuting Authority has confirmed the incident and that the two men will appear in the Middelburg Magistrate&#x2019;s Court on Wednesday. IOL